'''Martin Erlić''' ({{IPA|hr|mǎrtin êːrlitɕ}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1xvWBU%3D|title=Màrtin<sup>1</sup>|quote=Màrtin|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=19 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=fVZhURc%3D&keyword=jerlija|title=jèrlija|quote=Ȇrlić|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=19 March 2018|language=sh}}</ref> born 24 January&nbsp;1998) is a Croatian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|centre-back]] for the Danish club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Hailing from the village of {{ill|Tinj|hr}}, Erlić started training football at [[NK Raštane]] in a nearby village.{{Citation needed|date=April 2025}} At the age of 12, he was scouted by [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb]] and spent two years in its youth team before moving onto [[NK Rijeka]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2025}} Erlić moved abroad at the age of 16, to [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Ivica|last=Gjergja|title=Serie A i za reprezentaciju Hrvatske!|url=https://zadarski.slobodnadalmacija.hr/zadar/sport/martin-erlic-je-zbog-treninga-svakog-dana-pjeske-isao-od-tinja-do-rastana-a-sada-igra-u-talijanskoj-serie-a-i-za-reprezentaciju-hrvatske-1094957|url-status=live|newspaper=[[Slobodna Dalmacija]]|date=29 May 2021|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221208182815/https://zadarski.slobodnadalmacija.hr/zadar/sport/martin-erlic-je-zbog-treninga-svakog-dana-pjeske-isao-od-tinja-do-rastana-a-sada-igra-u-talijanskoj-serie-a-i-za-reprezentaciju-hrvatske-1094957|archive-date=8 December 2022}}</ref> After [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]]'s bankruptcy, Erlić went to [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] in 2015.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|first=Francesco|last=Oddi|title=Finale playoff: da Gyasi a Nzola, gli (altri) talenti da seguire in Spezia-Frosinone|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/fantanews/20-08-2020/finale-playoff-gyasi-nzola-altri-talenti-seguire-spezia-frosinone-3801306317899.shtml|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|publisher=[[RCS MediaGroup]]|date=20 August 2020|access-date=2 April 2025|language=it}}</ref>

==== Loan to Südtirol ====
On 31 August 2017, Erlić moved to [[Serie C]] club [[F.C. Südtirol|Südtirol]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Riccardo|last=Rimondi|title=Martin Erlić al Bologna: l'affidabilità già nota a Italiano, l'utilità in ottica lista UEFA, la disponibilità ad accettare il ruolo di quarto centrale|url=https://www.zerocinquantuno.it/notizie/calciomercato/martin-erlic-al-bologna-affidabilita-gia-nota-a-italiano-utilita-in-ottica-lista-uefa-la-disponibilita-ad-accettare-il-ruolo-di-quarto-centrale/|website=zerocinquantuno.it|date=4 August 2024|access-date=2 April 2025|language=it}}</ref> On 8 October, he made his Serie C debut for Südtirol, as a substitute replacing [[Filippo Sgarbi]] in the 70th minute of a 3–1 away defeat against [[Calcio Padova|Padova]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Südtirol vs. Padova|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/08/italy/serie-c1/biancoscudati-padova/fc-sudtirol-bolzano/2579453/|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|date=8 October 2017}}</ref>{{Better source needed|date=April 2025}} On 15 October, Erlić played his first entire match for Südtirol, a 5–0 home victory against [[Santarcangelo Calcio|Santarcangelo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/15/italy/serie-c1/fc-sudtirol-bolzano/asd-santarcangelo/2579465/|title=Südtirol vs. Santarcangelo|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|date=15 October 2017|access-date=30 November 2017}}</ref> On 8 November, Erlić scored his first professional goal for Südtirol in the 81st minute of a 1–0 away win over [[S.S. Sambenedettese Calcio|Sambenedettese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/11/08/italy/serie-c1/ss-sambenedettese-calcio/fc-sudtirol-bolzano/2579500/|title=Sambenedettese vs. Südtirol|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|date=8 November 2017|access-date=30 November 2017}}</ref> Erlić ended his season-long loan to Südtirol with 30 appearances as well as one goal and assist each.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/martin-erlic/396283/|title=M. Erlić|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|access-date=13 July 2018}}</ref>

===Later career===
On 10 July 2018, Erlić initially was loaned to Serie B club Spezia on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mercato Spezia, arriva dal Sassuolo il difensore Erlić|url=https://www.ligurianotizie.it/mercato-spezia-arriva-dal-sassuolo-il-difensore-eric/2018/07/12/303391/|website=Liguria Notizie|date=12 July 2018|access-date=2 April 2025|language=it}}</ref> After missing most of the 2018–19 season through the injury,<ref name=":0" /> he rejoined [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] on a permanent basis on 15 July 2019.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=[[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]]|url=https://www.acspezia.com/news/mercato-martin-erlic-ancora-in-maglia-bianca.20302.html|title=Mercato: Martin Erlic ancora in maglia bianca|date=15 July 2019|language=it}}</ref> Erlić signed for [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on 16 August 2021, but was returned on loan to Spezia for the 2021–22 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Spezia|url=https://www.acspezia.com/it/news/martin-erlic-a-titolo-definitivo-al-sassuolo.22797.html|title=Martin Erlić a Titolo Definitivo al Sassuolo|date=16 August 2021|access-date=2 July 2022|language=it}}</ref> On 2 August 2024, he signed with [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] in [[Serie A]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Martin Erlić Joins Bologna|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/en/martin-erlic-joins-bologna/|website=Bologna FC 1909|date=2 August 2024|access-date=16 August 2024}}</ref>

On 4 August 2025, Erlić signed a five-year contract with [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in Denmark.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Midtjylland|url=https://www.fcm.dk/nyheder/fc-midtjylland-koeber-martin-erlic/|title=FC Midtjylland køber Martin Erlić|trans-title=FC Midtjylland buys Martin Erlić|date=4 August 2025|access-date=4 August 2025|language=da}}</ref>

== International career ==
On 6 June 2022, Erlić made his debut for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]] in a 1–1 draw with [[France national football team|France]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A#Group 1|Nations League]].<ref name="index">{{Cite web |date=6 June 2022 |title=Erlić: Brat mi se ženio, a ja nisam otišao na vjenčanje zbog Hrvatske |url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2370184 |access-date=7 June 2022 |website=[[Index.hr]] |language=hr}}</ref> He stated to attend his brother's wedding to play the match.<ref name="index"/> On 9 November 2022, Erlić was named in [[Zlatko Dalić]]'s [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|26-man squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dalic-objavio-popis-za-svjetsko-prvenstvo-u-kataru/2410337.aspx |title=Dalić objavio popis za Svjetsko prvenstvo u Kataru |website=[[Index.hr]]|date=9 November 2022|access-date=18 December 2022|language=hr}}</ref> where he remained an unused substitute as Croatia finished third.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/pet-igraca-hrvatske-nije-dobilo-ni-minutu-na-svjetskom-prvenstvu/2421887.aspx |title=Pet igrača Hrvatske nije dobilo ni minutu na Svjetskom prvenstvu |website=[[Index.hr]]|date=17 December 2022|access-date=18 December 2022|language=hr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Erlić is a fan of [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.acspezia.com/news/comunicato-ufficiale-martin-erlic.21879.html|title=Comunicato ufficiale: Martin Erlić|publisher=[[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]]|date=24 October 2020|access-date=25 October 2020}}</ref>{{Better source needed|date=April 2025}}

